lead_paragraph: A two-week meeting opened here today to prepare an agenda for a new 35-nation European security conference that is to open in November. Delegations from 35 nations - the United States, Canada and all the European countries apart from Albania -began preparing the agenda and timetable for the conference, the third follow-up meeting in the so-called Helsinki process, which was begun in 1975. The only public sessions so far agreed to for November are speeches by the delegation leaders.

headline.main: TALKS ARE BEGUN ON VIENNA AGENDA
